init_text: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They had never been aware of it before, but the process of a bee whispering into your ear was fairly uncomfortable.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They could not fight bees from beyond the grave, anyway.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They would be allowed to set up a hive of their own, as long as they did not bother them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The bees would have a home and the allergic man could continue on with his life without worrying about being stung.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The allergic man and his family were relieved to be able to live free of worry.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: As the bees grew in number, and as they were a part of the family now, they knew there was something that would threaten their way

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They would finally have their freedom to rule over all that they could see.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They were a scourge upon the land and would not stop until they had complete control.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The family settled down in the land of the ice and snow.
